Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows evidence of renal dysfunction (elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria), hypoglycemia (low blood glucose and HbA1c), metabolic acidosis (low COâ‚‚), and abnormal urinalysis (glucosuria, ketonuria, proteinuria, low specific gravity, brown cloudy urine). These findings suggest possible acute or chronic kidney disease with glycosuria and ketonuria not explained by hyperglycemia, warranting urgent clinical evaluation for underlying metabolic, renal, or systemic disorders.
